Depending on the situation, you may also place

This event is used to change Serena's standing

The VP (visual presentation) and screen effects
can be expressed using variables and common
events, separate from direct input.

By inputting variables corresponding to each event
in variables 925-928 and executing Common Events
391-394, you can play sound effects (SE)
corresponding to each situation.

When you want to repeat the SE, repeat it as many
times as the number entered in variable 932 (the
SE that will be repeated is randomly played and
sounds appropriate).

Regarding flash and screen effects, they can be
expressed by executing variable 933 and Common
Event 397.

Please refer to the relevant section of the recent
ci-en article titled Regarding Modifications for
detailed information.

You can also use BGS (background sound) to
continuously play sound effects, so please feel
free to create events according to your
preferences without being limited to the above
functions.

I summarized each SE that seems useful for copy-
pasting.

Currently, the VP (visual presentation) is in a
very unstable operating environment, and even when
creating events, it becomes a state where it
crashes one out of every two times during data
saving.

Therefore, if you don't perform processes such as
saving the created event information externally
before saving, the work will not progress
properly.

As for the method, you can start RPG Maker twice,
one for creating events and the other for using it
as a primary data backup to prevent accidents
caused by forced termination.
